Author: Wang, Z.
Nelson, J. K.
Hillborg, H.
Zhao, S.
Schadler, L. S.
Keyword: graphene oxide filled silicone rubber nanocomposites
CommonFields.Location: Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, NY 12180, USA

Width.description: The average lateral dimension of GO was about 500 nm.

Length.description: The average lateral dimension of GO was about 500 nm.

Depth.description: The average thickness was 1.1 nm indicating mostly monolayer GO.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The suspension was freeze-dried for 2 days

Heating.Description: thermally reduced at temperature of 70 °C 12 hours. The temperature ramp rate was kept at 0.5 °C/min to avoid violent reduction of GO.

Mixing.Description: the precursor Sylgard 184A using a FlackTek Speed Mixer at 3000 rpm for a total of 30 minutes in 6 intermittent runs.

Additive.Description: Then Sylgard 184B was added into the mixture

MoldingInfo.Description: curing in a mould at 150 °C for 1 hour

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Equipment: Novocontrol alpha high resolution dielectric impedance analyzer
Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: The composite samples were tested in a Novocontrol alpha high resolution dielectric impedance analyzer for dielectric spectroscopy at room temperature.

Electrometry.Description: The absorption current and conductivity measurements were carried out in a guarded cell connected to a high voltage DC power supply and Keithley picoammeter. In the conductivity measurement, the field strength was stepped up to 10 kV/mm at an interval of 0.5 kV/mm. Conductivity data were taken as a function of field strength after holding the voltage constant for 30 minutes.
